<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="491" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,474,933]" pageId="6" pageNumber="491">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,498,618,645]" pageId="6" pageNumber="491">Distribution and ecology</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[515,663,619,645]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1880,1904]" captionTargetBox="[307,1281,181,1843]" captionTargetId="figure-17@5.[307,1281,181,1856]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4. Nemoura habitats in Qinghai, China. A. Habitat of Nemoura jixiangwangi sp. nov. and Nemoura securigera Klapálek, 1907: Deqian Village. B. Habitat of Nemoura jixiangwangi sp. nov.: Dayu Village. C. Habitat of Nemoura geei Wu, 1929 and Nemoura papilla Okamoto, 1922: Sigou. D. Habitat of Nemoura papilla Okamoto, 1922: Huzhu County, Weibei Highway. E–F. Habitat of Nemoura securigera Klapálek, 1907: Qihankaigou (Qihankai valley), main river and sidestream." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6899855" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6899855/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="491">Figs. 4a, e–f</figureCitation>
). The species is known only from 
<collectingCountry box="[1062,1133,619,645]" name="China" pageId="6" pageNumber="491">China</collectingCountry>
: 
<collectingRegion box="[1146,1284,619,645]" country="China" name="Nei Mongol" pageId="6" pageNumber="491">Nei Mongol</collectingRegion>
Autonomous Region, 
<collectingRegion box="[246,336,655,681]" country="China" name="Qinghai" pageId="6" pageNumber="491">Qinghai</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion box="[390,480,655,681]" country="China" name="Shaanxi" pageId="6" pageNumber="491">Shaanxi</collectingRegion>
provinces (
<bibRefCitation author="Yang, D. &amp; Li, W. H." box="[611,799,655,681]" pageId="6" pageNumber="491" refId="ref4770" refString="Yang, D. &amp; Li, W. H. (2018) Species Catalogue of China. Volume 2 Animals, Insecta (III), Plecoptera. Science Press, Beijing, 71 pp." type="book" year="2018">Yang &amp; Li 2018</bibRefCitation>
). It was redescribed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Li, W. H. &amp; Muranyi D. &amp; Pan J. J. &amp; Yang, D." box="[1063,1232,655,681]" pageId="6" pageNumber="491" pagination="473 - 480" refId="ref3408" refString="Li, W. H., Muranyi D., Pan J. J. &amp; Yang, D. (2013) New and little known species of Nemouridae (Plecoptera) from Inner Mongolia of China. Zootaxa, 3746 (3), 473 - 480. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3746.3.6" type="journal article" year="2013">
Li 
<emphasis box="[1094,1151,655,681]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="491">et al.</emphasis>
(2013)
</bibRefCitation>
from 
<collectingRegion box="[1300,1437,655,681]" country="China" name="Nei Mongol" pageId="6" pageNumber="491">Nei Mongol</collectingRegion>
under the name 
<taxonomicName authority="Klapalek, 1907" authorityName="Klapalek" authorityYear="1907" box="[334,783,691,717]" class="Insecta" family="Nemouridae" genus="Nemoura" isUncertain="true" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="491" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="securigera">
<emphasis box="[334,601,691,717]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="491">Nemoura cf. securigera</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Klapalek, F." box="[609,783,691,717]" pageId="6" pageNumber="491" pagination="59 - 64" refId="ref3273" refString="Klapalek, F. (1907) Plecoptera. In: Wissenschaftliche Ergebnisse der Expedition Filchner nach China und Tibet 1903 - 1905. Wissenschaftliche Zoologische Botanische Ergebnisse, 10, 59 - 64. https: // doi. org / 10.2307 / 199584" type="journal article" year="1907">Klapálek, 1907</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. We recently found this species at several localities in the Qinling Mountain, 
<collectingRegion box="[368,461,727,753]" country="China" name="Shaanxi" pageId="6" pageNumber="491">Shaanxi</collectingRegion>
, the 
<typeStatus box="[516,564,727,753]" pageId="6" pageNumber="491">type</typeStatus>
locality of the species (unpublished data). We believe that the populations in 
<collectingRegion box="[151,290,763,789]" country="China" name="Nei Mongol" pageId="6" pageNumber="491">Nei Mongol</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion box="[348,438,763,789]" country="China" name="Qinghai" pageId="6" pageNumber="491">Qinghai</collectingRegion>
represent the same species as the Qinling populations. The species was never found in Qinling during summer surveys of recent years, but occurs during summer in 
<collectingRegion box="[1024,1160,799,825]" country="China" name="Nei Mongol" pageId="6" pageNumber="491">Nei Mongol</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion box="[1215,1309,799,825]" country="China" name="Qinghai" pageId="6" pageNumber="491">Qinghai</collectingRegion>
. It emerges from early April 
<collectingRegion box="[346,485,835,861]" country="China" name="Nei Mongol" pageId="6" pageNumber="491">Nei Mongol</collectingRegion>
and Qinling (unpublished data). Two of the 
<collectingRegion box="[998,1088,835,861]" country="China" name="Qinghai" pageId="6" pageNumber="491">Qinghai</collectingRegion>
males were collected together with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Yan &amp; Ma &amp; Yang &amp; Li" authorityYear="2022" box="[209,389,871,896]" class="Insecta" family="Nemouridae" genus="Nemoura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="491" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jixiangwangi">
<emphasis box="[209,389,871,896]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="491">N. jixiangwangi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
at Deqian village (
<figureCitation box="[606,689,871,897]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1880,1904]" captionTargetBox="[307,1281,181,1843]" captionTargetId="figure-17@5.[307,1281,181,1856]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4. Nemoura habitats in Qinghai, China. A. Habitat of Nemoura jixiangwangi sp. nov. and Nemoura securigera Klapálek, 1907: Deqian Village. B. Habitat of Nemoura jixiangwangi sp. nov.: Dayu Village. C. Habitat of Nemoura geei Wu, 1929 and Nemoura papilla Okamoto, 1922: Sigou. D. Habitat of Nemoura papilla Okamoto, 1922: Huzhu County, Weibei Highway. E–F. Habitat of Nemoura securigera Klapálek, 1907: Qihankaigou (Qihankai valley), main river and sidestream." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6899855" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6899855/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="491">Fig. 4a</figureCitation>
), and another one was found in a forest stream at Qihankai valley (
<figureCitation box="[159,242,907,933]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1880,1904]" captionTargetBox="[307,1281,181,1843]" captionTargetId="figure-17@5.[307,1281,181,1856]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4. Nemoura habitats in Qinghai, China. A. Habitat of Nemoura jixiangwangi sp. nov. and Nemoura securigera Klapálek, 1907: Deqian Village. B. Habitat of Nemoura jixiangwangi sp. nov.: Dayu Village. C. Habitat of Nemoura geei Wu, 1929 and Nemoura papilla Okamoto, 1922: Sigou. D. Habitat of Nemoura papilla Okamoto, 1922: Huzhu County, Weibei Highway. E–F. Habitat of Nemoura securigera Klapálek, 1907: Qihankaigou (Qihankai valley), main river and sidestream." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6899855" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6899855/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="491">Fig. 4e</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
